^BOP Button Opacity Command. Set the button opacity in the selected state(s)
Syntax:
"^BOP-<vt addr range>,<button state range>,<opacity>"
Variables:
Variable text addr range = 1-4000
button states range = 1 - 256 for multi-state buttons (0 = All states, for General buttons 1 = Off state and 2 =
On state).
opacity is an integer value from 0-255 where 0 is fully transparent and 255 is fully opaque, or #XX where the
value after the # is a HEX number between 0 and FF.
Example:
SEND_COMMAND Panel,"'^BOP-500.504&510.515,1,200'"
Example 2:
SEND_COMMAND Panel,"'^BOP-500.504&510.515,1,#C8'"
Both examples set the opacity of the buttons with the variable text range of 500-504 and 510-515 to 200.
^BOS Button State Video Fill Command. Sets the button state to display either a Video or Non-Video window.
Syntax:
"'^BOS-<vt addr range>,<button states range>,<video state>'"
Variable:
variable text address range = 1 - 4000.
button states range = 1 - 256 for multi-state buttons (0 = All states, for General buttons. 1 = Off state and 2 =
On state.
video state = Video Off = 0, URL Video On = 1, MPL Video On = 101.
Example:
SEND_COMMAND Panel,"'^BOS-500,1,1'"
Sets the button to display video.
?BOS Query Button State Video Fill Command. Get the current button state video fill.
Syntax:
"'?BOS-<vt addr range>,<button states range>'"
Variables:
variable text address range = 1 - 4000.
button states range = 1 - 256 for multi-state buttons (0 = All states, for General buttons 1 = Off state and 2 =
On state).
The response returned is a custom event with the following syntax:
